    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p><strong>Speed</strong>&nbsp;30 ft., <strong>fly </strong>40 ft. (poor)<br /><strong>Strength&nbsp;</strong>26 (+8);&nbsp;<strong>Damage&nbsp;</strong>4d6 S or P;&nbsp;<strong>Size&nbsp;</strong>Medium<br /><strong>Capacity&nbsp;</strong>20;&nbsp;<strong>Usage&nbsp;</strong>1/hour</p>\n<p>Inspired by the angel frame, devaplate is a purely technological wonder. Its featureless faceplate provides a sophisticated heads-up display that allows the wearer to see as if they possessed darkvision 120 ft. and low-light vision, includes an integrated @Compendium[sfrpg.equipment.sBXU59RIx5BRkrbN]{MedObserve} armor upgrade, and grants a +2 circumstance bonus on saving throws to resist harmful visual effects. Devaplate&rsquo;s specialized shielding grants the wearer resistance 10 against acid, cold, electricity, fire, and positive and negative energy damage. The armor&rsquo;s user-monitoring systems detect when the wearer is poisoned and auto-inject counteragents, granting a +2 enhancement bonus to saves against @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.JaRMioj4isNp7r1P.JournalEntryPage.ZaS9H4rwaFIQTUBC]{poison}. Finally, while the wearer is not using the armor&rsquo;s fly speed, they can angle the suit&rsquo;s wings to project defensive fields and deflect projectiles, acting as an integrated @Compendium[sfrpg.equipment.zYYCYrG9KKD1hzSe]{titan shield} armor upgrade.</p>"
